WEBVTT

00:04.938 --> 00:06.540 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening. I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.573 --> 00:11.278 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: We sit down with
the U.K. defense secretary to discuss how

00:11.311 --> 00:15.082 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a growing coalition could change the fight
against ISIS.

00:15.115 --> 00:18.719 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON, U.K. Defense Secretary: This
was never going to be a quick campaign. It

00:18.752 --> 00:24.558 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was your own Secretary Kerry who said he thought
the campaign in Iraq might last at least three

00:24.591 --> 00:28.729 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
years, and we're not halfway through that
yet. But progress is being made.

00:28.762 --> 00:33.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Then: how Muslims in America
are faring against a climate of fear.

00:33.700 --> 00:37.571 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AYA LAOFIR, High School Student: As I'm walking,
and I see people, they duck their heads, or

00:37.604 --> 00:42.009 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
when I smile at them, they don't smile back,
I'm just like, oh, is it because I'm wearing

00:42.042 --> 00:44.211 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
my scarf? Is it because of what's on the news?

00:44.244 --> 00:49.249 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And it's Friday. Mark Shields
and David Brooks join us to analyze the week's

00:49.283 --> 00:50.183 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
news.

00:50.217 --> 00:57.124 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
All that and more on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:57.157 --> 01:00.027 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:00.060 --> 01:10.570 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The U.S. government will remain
open, for now. Congress today sent President

01:10.604 --> 01:16.576 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Obama a short-term spending bill to fund agencies
through next Wednesday. The move buys more

01:16.610 --> 01:23.050 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
time to negotiate a $1.1 trillion long-term
tax and spending bill.

01:23.083 --> 01:28.355 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
House lawmakers on both sides remained optimistic
that a budget deal could be reached by next

01:28.388 --> 01:30.223 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
week.

01:30.257 --> 01:31.959 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
REP. JARED POLIS (D), Colorado: The Republicans
have previously shown this country their willingness

01:31.992 --> 01:37.864 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to go into a shutdown. So, I hope that we
take this new five-day period to avoid a shutdown

01:37.898 --> 01:41.802 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
permanently, rather than just to do another
three or five days again and again and again.

01:41.835 --> 01:47.574 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
REP. TOM COLE (R), Oklahoma: Writing a $1.1
trillion omnibus bill takes a lot of time.

01:47.607 --> 01:52.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there's multiple items to be negotiated.
Now, I think both sides is negotiating in

01:52.579 --> 01:56.516 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
good faith in this legislative body, and I
think the administration is participating

01:56.550 --> 01:58.151 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in good faith.

01:58.185 --> 02:02.823 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Negotiators remain divided,
though, over additional unrelated provisions

02:02.856 --> 02:07.761 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that some lawmakers are trying to attach to
the bill. They include new environmental rules

02:07.794 --> 02:13.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on carbon emissions and efforts to stem the
flow of Syrian refugees into the United States.

02:13.834 --> 02:19.373 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Two giants in the chemical industry, DuPont
and Dow Chemical, have officially announced

02:19.406 --> 02:26.646 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they're merging. The fusion of two of America's
oldest companies is valued at $130 billion.

02:26.680 --> 02:32.552 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The new entity will be split into three separate
companies, focused on agriculture, materials,

02:32.586 --> 02:38.158 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and specialty products. But the deal still
requires the approval of federal regulators.

02:38.191 --> 02:45.532 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The price of oil plunged to near seven-year
lows today. It closed at $35.62 a barrel in

02:45.565 --> 02:51.938 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
New York, down more than 3 percent. The drop
has been driven by increased U.S. production,

02:51.972 --> 02:57.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an abundant global supply, and the strength
of the U.S. dollar. And it triggered a sell-off

02:57.444 --> 03:06.219 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on Wall Street. The Dow Jones industrial average
plummeted over 309 points to close at 17265.

03:06.253 --> 03:11.658 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell more than 111 points, and
the S&amp;P 500 lost nearly 40 points.

03:11.691 --> 03:18.365 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the week, the Nasdaq and the S&amp;P were
down roughly 4 percent. The Dow fell more

03:18.398 --> 03:20.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
than 3 percent.

03:20.367 --> 03:27.140 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
High-stakes global climate talks on the outskirts
of Paris are dragging into an extra day. Negotiations

03:27.174 --> 03:32.846 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
were scheduled to wrap today, but disagreements
remain over who should bear the most burden

03:32.879 --> 03:39.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in reducing emissions and whether rich countries
should be responsible for most of the cost.

03:39.219 --> 03:45.292 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Diplomats from over 190 nations were trying
to reach a deal, and the summit's president,

03:45.325 --> 03:49.196 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
French Foreign Minister Laurent Fabius, said
the time is right.

03:49.229 --> 03:52.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LAURENT FABIUS, French Foreign Minister (through
translator): All the conditions are there

03:52.332 --> 03:57.471 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for us to reach a universal, ambitious agreement,
and observers will recognize that the conditions

03:57.504 --> 04:02.442 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have probably never been so favorable. Now
it's the ministers' responsibility to make

04:02.476 --> 04:04.077 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
their choice tomorrow.

04:04.111 --> 04:08.949 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Fabius is expected to present
a new version of the draft accord Saturday

04:08.982 --> 04:10.684 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
morning.

04:10.717 --> 04:15.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Heightened security measures remained in place
in Geneva, Switzerland today, amid an ongoing

04:15.188 --> 04:21.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hunt for possible terror suspects linked to
the Islamic State. At Geneva's airport, bomb

04:21.261 --> 04:28.635 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
squads detonated abandoned luggage as a precaution.
A few miles away, armed guards remained vigilant

04:28.668 --> 04:31.338 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
outside the United Nations building.

04:31.371 --> 04:35.041 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Officials warned the enhanced security could
last for the foreseeable future.

04:35.075 --> 04:37.144 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PIERRE MAUDET, Geneva Minister of Economy
and Security (through translator): For us,

04:37.177 --> 04:40.981 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this is a pretty sustained effort for police
forces. There are actions in several parts

04:41.014 --> 04:45.385 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the town: bomb alerts, a need to reinforce
police troops, and we have the capacity to

04:45.418 --> 04:47.854 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
maintain this level for a certain number of
days.

04:47.888 --> 04:52.526 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Authorities said they're searching
for at least four suspects believed to be

04:52.559 --> 04:58.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
plotting a specific attack in the city. Local
news media reported the two Syrian nationals

04:58.732 --> 05:04.437 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
were arrested today in Geneva after traces
of explosives were found in their car, but

05:04.471 --> 05:07.841 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it's not clear if they were linked to the
manhunt.

05:07.874 --> 05:13.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Back in this country, officials are scouring
for red flags they missed before last week's

05:13.046 --> 05:17.851 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
shooting in San Bernardino. The Associated
Press reported that authorities didn't pick

05:17.884 --> 05:23.690 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
up on extremist messages that were exchanged
online between the two killers, Syed Farook

05:23.723 --> 05:26.860 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and Tashfeen Malik, two years ago.

05:26.893 --> 05:33.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Meanwhile, an FBI dive team again searched
a small lake some three miles from the attack

05:33.633 --> 05:38.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
site, looking for a computer hard drive that
may have been dumped.

05:39.005 --> 05:44.277 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there were competing court rulings in
New York today over two daily fantasy sports

05:44.311 --> 05:50.550 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Web sites. At first, a judge banned the sites
DraftKings and FanDuel from doing business

05:50.584 --> 05:55.722 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the state. That was after New York's attorney
general argued that the games were illegal

05:55.755 --> 06:01.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gambling. But, later, a state appeals court
judge said the sites could continue to operate

06:01.228 --> 06:05.498 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for now, while the issue is fully considered.

06:05.532 --> 06:09.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour": the British
defense secretary on joining the fight against

06:09.903 --> 06:17.310 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS; a swift backlash against Muslims in
America; the human cost of building the nation's

06:17.344 --> 06:31.358 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
nuclear arsenal; and much more.

06:31.391 --> 06:35.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The United States and its coalition partners
have been fighting the Islamic State group

06:35.662 --> 06:40.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for 16 months to beat back the group's gains
in both Syria and Iraq.

06:40.934 --> 06:46.940 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
At the same time, Syria's many-sided civil
war continues unabated. Russia has inserted

06:46.973 --> 06:52.879 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
itself to support the regime of its ally President
Bashar al-Assad. And last week, the United

06:52.912 --> 06:58.852 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Kingdom said that it would join the U.S. and
France in bombing Islamic State in Syria as

06:58.885 --> 07:02.222 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the militant group has begun attacks on the
West.

07:02.255 --> 07:07.627 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All this comes as a major diplomatic push
to end the nearly-five-year-old brutal war

07:07.661 --> 07:12.098 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is under way, and the American and British
defense secretaries at the Pentagon.

07:12.132 --> 07:16.803 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ASHTON CARTER, U.S. Defense Secretary: We
will defeat ISIL, and we will ensure that

07:16.836 --> 07:18.571 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
they stay defeated.

07:18.605 --> 07:23.977 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Secretary of Defense Ash Carter
hosted his British counterpart, Michael Fallon,

07:24.010 --> 07:28.682 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to chart the coalition's progress in the campaign
against the Islamic State group.

07:28.715 --> 07:35.088 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Fallon said British sorties have been aimed
at ISIS fighters and the oil fields the group

07:35.121 --> 07:41.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
uses, in part, to finance itself. After the
Paris attacks, as France began airstrikes

07:41.394 --> 07:49.169 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Syria, Britain's Parliament approved expanding
the U.K.'s existing Iraq air campaign into

07:49.202 --> 07:51.071 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Syria as well.

07:51.104 --> 07:57.577 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Meanwhile, today in Moscow, Russian President
Vladimir Putin spoke about his country's war

07:57.610 --> 08:04.617 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Syria. For the first time, he said that
Russian aircraft are now helping a rebel group,

08:04.651 --> 08:06.886 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the U.S.-backed Free Syrian Army.

08:06.920 --> 08:10.156 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
VLADIMIR PUTIN, Russian President (through
translator): The activities of our aviation

08:10.190 --> 08:14.661 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
group assists in uniting the efforts of government
troops and the Free Syrian Army.

08:14.694 --> 08:19.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back in Washington, State Department
spokesman John Kirby said those claims were

08:19.999 --> 08:26.873 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
unverified, but noted that, in the past, Russia
has targeted those groups. Fallon echoed Kirby

08:26.906 --> 08:28.541 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on that point.

08:28.575 --> 08:30.777 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON, U.K. Defense Secretary: What
they have got to do is stop propping up the

08:30.810 --> 08:36.483 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Assad regime, stop bombing opposition groups
who are opposed to the Assad regime, stop

08:36.516 --> 08:43.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
dropping unguided munitions on innocent villages
and groups who have been fighting Assad, and

08:44.023 --> 08:47.227 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
get behind the political process that is now
under way.

08:47.260 --> 08:52.098 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Earlier today, I sat down with
Britain's defense secretary to discuss the

08:52.132 --> 08:57.637 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
war effort at the residence of the British
ambassador here in Washington.

08:57.670 --> 09:00.173 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Defense Secretary Michael Fallon, thank you
very much for talking with us.

09:00.206 --> 09:01.875 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Good morning.

09:01.908 --> 09:05.478 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, for Americans who weren't
following closely the vote in your Parliament

09:05.512 --> 09:13.586 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
last week to authorize the expansion of airstrikes
against ISIS from Iraq into Syria, what was

09:13.620 --> 09:20.593 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it that led to the decision to go against
what had seemed to be an anti-interventionist

09:20.627 --> 09:22.362 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
policy in your country?

09:22.395 --> 09:26.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, I think a growing recognition
that this border between Iraq and Syria is

09:26.566 --> 09:32.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not recognized by ISIL itself, and it's completely
artificial and rather odd to be carrying out

09:33.006 --> 09:37.310 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
airstrikes on one side of the border, but
the Royal Air Force having to turn back at

09:37.343 --> 09:40.647 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the border and not follow through the other
side of the border.

09:40.680 --> 09:46.319 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was also a response to France and the United
States and other countries that wanted Britain

09:46.352 --> 09:51.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to step up its contribution to the campaign.
And I'm delighted we're now able to do that.

09:51.558 --> 09:56.129 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have doubled the number of strike aircraft
that we have in theater. And we're upping

09:56.162 --> 09:57.797 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the tempo of our missions.

09:57.831 --> 10:01.468 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You started the air campaign
right away, after the vote. It just happened

10:01.501 --> 10:06.406 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
within hours. What have been the main targets
and how successful has it been so far?

10:06.439 --> 10:11.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: We have focused those strikes
very much on the infrastructure that supports

10:11.444 --> 10:19.385 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS, the oil wells, for example, the supply
routes, the depots, the arms dumps, the logistics,

10:19.419 --> 10:24.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the command and control, because we need to
degrade the infrastructure and the revenue

10:24.757 --> 10:26.826 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that supports the supporting organization.

10:26.860 --> 10:29.062 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Has it been -- how successful
has it been?

10:29.095 --> 10:31.631 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: The strikes we have carried
out so far have been successful. They have

10:31.664 --> 10:37.170 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
been mainly in the oil fields of Eastern Syria.
We have been hitting oil wellheads, and those

10:37.203 --> 10:39.138 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
strikes, yes, have been successful.

10:39.172 --> 10:46.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The question then arises, there's
been an air campaign in Iraq against ISIS

10:46.412 --> 10:53.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for a year or more. There's been some progress,
but it's been limited. What makes you believe

10:53.219 --> 10:58.358 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that expanding into Syria, that this campaign
is going to be any more successful?

10:58.391 --> 11:02.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, this was never going
to be a quick campaign. It was your own Secretary

11:02.395 --> 11:07.834 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Kerry who said he thought the campaign in
Iraq might last at least three years, and

11:07.867 --> 11:11.137 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we're not halfway through that yet, but progress
is being made.

11:11.170 --> 11:16.809 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But can ISIS be defeated with
an air campaign? Are ground forces going to

11:16.843 --> 11:20.413 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
be necessary for this to work in the end?

11:20.446 --> 11:24.183 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, ground forces are being
deployed in Iraq, where there is the Iraqi

11:24.217 --> 11:30.490 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
army, there are Kurdish forces who are helping
to liberate these towns, like Tikrit and Baiji,

11:30.523 --> 11:34.827 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
which have already fallen. And ISIL have been
pushed back out of those towns.

11:34.861 --> 11:39.499 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now, we want eventually the same to happen
on the Syrian side of this very artificial

11:39.532 --> 11:46.639 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
line. But, meantime, there's a lot that airstrikes
can do to help cut off ISIS' source of revenue

11:46.673 --> 11:50.677 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and to help squeeze the noose around its headquarters
in Raqqa.

11:50.710 --> 11:56.082 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, when is the right time
for there to be a larger ground force presence

11:56.115 --> 12:00.620 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Syria, and will Britain be part of that,
will the U.K. be part of that?

12:00.653 --> 12:04.757 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: We're not going to put our
own troops on the ground there. And, indeed,

12:04.791 --> 12:08.094 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Iraq, they have made it very clear they
don't want British or even -- with respect,

12:08.127 --> 12:12.465 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they don't want American troops there, because
they feel that would simply radicalize Sunni

12:12.498 --> 12:14.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
opinion even more.

12:14.267 --> 12:20.273 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In the end, this has to be done -- this territory
has to be liberated and held by local forces

12:20.306 --> 12:26.479 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that enjoy the confidence of the local community,
particularly the Sunni areas. And that has

12:26.512 --> 12:31.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to be done locally. And the way to do that
is to bring the civil war to an end and to

12:31.217 --> 12:36.789 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
use moderate Syrian groups to help defeat
ISIS up in the northeast corner.

12:36.823 --> 12:40.493 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But hasn't that been a goal
for a long time, and it just hasn't been achieved?

12:40.526 --> 12:44.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, just in the last few
months, we have seen real progress there,

12:44.530 --> 12:49.435 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
everybody involved now coming together, a
conference in Saudi Arabia this week, just

12:49.469 --> 12:54.941 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this week, bringing all the parties involved,
and countries like Russia, Iran, Saudi Arabia

12:54.974 --> 13:01.414 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that all have an interest now beginning to
think their way through to a new Syria that

13:01.447 --> 13:03.016 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is without Assad.

13:03.049 --> 13:07.720 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But Assad, President Assad,
shows no desire whatsoever to leave. He's

13:07.754 --> 13:14.961 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
been supported completely by Russia and by
Iran. Is there new indication that that support

13:14.994 --> 13:17.330 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
has changed, is falling away?

13:17.363 --> 13:21.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Yes, we're beginning to see
signs that that is weakening. People are beginning

13:21.100 --> 13:26.906 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to think their way towards a different kind
of Syria and recognize that he can't be part

13:26.939 --> 13:28.641 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the long-term future.

13:28.675 --> 13:33.946 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Is Russia's involvement militarily
in Syria helping this campaign or hurting

13:33.980 --> 13:35.581 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it?

13:35.615 --> 13:38.017 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: It's extremely unhelpful,
because, of course, they came into the civil

13:38.051 --> 13:44.023 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
war, and they have been bombing moderate opposition
groups that have been standing up to Assad,

13:44.057 --> 13:47.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
instead of attacking ISIS alongside the rest
of us.

13:47.326 --> 13:50.563 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let me ask you about domestic
terrorism.

13:50.596 --> 13:56.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Your country has -- saw the real threat of
domestic terrorism well before the United

13:56.903 --> 14:03.976 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
States did with this most recent attack in
San Bernardino. What lessons has Great Britain,

14:04.010 --> 14:07.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has the United Kingdom learned from your own
experience?

14:07.046 --> 14:11.350 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, we have seen these -- alongside
your own shooting, we have had these terrible

14:11.384 --> 14:17.090 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
shootings in Paris just two hours away from
us, and earlier in the summer, we had 30 of

14:17.123 --> 14:21.327 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
our own holiday-makers slaughtered on a beach
in Tunisia.

14:21.360 --> 14:28.267 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So this is very real to us. These attacks
are directed, organized, inspired, financed

14:28.301 --> 14:33.506 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from ISIS in its headquarters in Syria. And
that's one reason why we have now committed

14:33.539 --> 14:38.244 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ourselves to this campaign in full across
both Iraq and Syria.

14:38.277 --> 14:43.449 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What about those individuals
who are inspired, who may not be directed

14:43.483 --> 14:50.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by ISIS, but who are inspired by their message,
by their philosophy to commit acts of terror

14:50.156 --> 14:51.758 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in your country?

14:51.791 --> 14:56.028 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, we have a program of
-- aimed at tackling radicalization. We call

14:56.062 --> 15:02.135 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it the Prevent program to try and identify
much earlier those who are likely to end up

15:02.168 --> 15:08.407 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as potential terrorists, to identify them
in the schools, at the colleges, in the madrasas,

15:08.441 --> 15:14.380 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and working with moderate Muslim communities
to see who these people are and see what we

15:14.413 --> 15:20.653 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can do to make sure they don't go along that
journey of being mildly, mildly Islamist to

15:20.686 --> 15:22.555 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
being extreme.

15:22.588 --> 15:30.897 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I think it's widely accepted
that there has been a greater effort to integrate

15:30.930 --> 15:38.404 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Muslims into U.S. society than there has been
in European countries, including the U.K.

15:38.437 --> 15:45.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Are there lessons that your country is learning
from the U.S. about integrating Muslims into

15:45.444 --> 15:49.649 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
society that makes you stronger when it comes
to standing up to this extremist...

15:49.682 --> 15:53.119 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Well, that is exactly the
challenge.

15:53.152 --> 15:58.724 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The United States is a great open society,
and you have found a way of embracing different

15:58.758 --> 16:05.598 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
faiths and different immigrants from different
countries and making them all Americans. And

16:05.631 --> 16:10.670 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we need to work harder than that -- about
that in Western Europe, and avoiding the kind

16:10.703 --> 16:17.043 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of ghettoization of different groups that
can lead to these tensions, and make it more

16:17.076 --> 16:20.379 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
difficult to challenge extremist behavior
later on.

16:20.413 --> 16:26.385 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Secretary of Defense Michael
Fallon, we thank you for talking with us.

16:26.419 --> 16:34.894 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICHAEL FALLON: Thank you.

16:34.927 --> 16:43.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now we get the perspective
of those Muslims in America, a community under

16:43.302 --> 16:45.972 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
assault in the wake of recent attacks.

16:46.005 --> 16:50.643 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Just this afternoon, there was a fire at a
mosque in Southern California. The imam said

16:50.676 --> 16:54.413 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there was a loud boom, and the building had
been firebombed.

16:54.447 --> 16:58.150 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is the latest in a string of violence directed
at Muslims.

16:58.184 --> 17:00.653 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The "NewsHour"'s P.J. Tobia has our story.

17:00.686 --> 17:08.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AYA LAOFIR, High School Student: I pray five
times a day, which I don't get to do at school,

17:08.394 --> 17:13.699 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but I come home and pray. I do my homework,
read a little bit, and then I go to bed.

17:13.733 --> 17:19.005 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Fifteen-year-old Aya Laofir, is
just like any other American teenager. At

17:19.038 --> 17:21.641 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
school, being Muslim just isn't a big deal.

17:21.674 --> 17:26.946 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AYA LAOFIR: Overall, I think, you know, school
is good when it comes to me and my scarf.

17:26.979 --> 17:30.683 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: But on the way home, sometimes,
there is trouble.

17:30.716 --> 17:35.521 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AYA LAOFIR: There is this man who sits on
the sidewalk sometimes, and he starts, you

17:35.554 --> 17:39.859 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know, harassing -- well, not harassing me,
well, calling me names and telling me to go

17:39.892 --> 17:41.494 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
back to my country.

17:41.527 --> 17:44.563 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: She lives in Northern Virginia,
one of the most culturally diverse regions

17:44.597 --> 17:46.232 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the nation, according to the last census.

17:46.265 --> 17:50.336 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AYA LAOFIR: As I'm walking, and I see people,
they duck their heads, or when I smile at

17:50.369 --> 17:54.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
them, they don't smile back, I'm just like,
oh, is it because I'm wearing my scarf? Is

17:54.340 --> 17:55.975 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it because of what's on the news?

17:56.008 --> 17:59.612 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: What's on the news is a series
of terrorist attacks, most recently in Paris,

17:59.645 --> 18:04.583 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
France, and San Bernardino, California, killings
in the name of the Islamic State.

18:04.617 --> 18:09.255 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In response, the temperature of America's
political climate is rising. Leading Republican

18:09.288 --> 18:14.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
presidential candidate Donald Trump has proposed
to temporarily ban all Muslims from entering

18:14.293 --> 18:19.632 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the country, a policy which one in four Americans
now support, according to an NBC poll.

18:19.665 --> 18:24.403 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's not just Trump. Other leading GOP
candidates have also made comments that have

18:24.437 --> 18:30.643 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
upset American Muslims. As a result, many
like Aya, now feel unsafe.

18:30.676 --> 18:34.880 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In Irving, Texas, one group has been holding
regular protests in front of an Islamic center

18:34.914 --> 18:40.453 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
since late November, brandishing semiautomatic
rifles, some wearing masks. The protesters

18:40.486 --> 18:44.223 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
want to stop what they call the Islamization
of America.

18:44.256 --> 18:48.594 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In Pittsburgh, a Moroccan immigrant taxi driver
was shot after his passenger asked him about

18:48.627 --> 18:52.999 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Islamic State. And in Northern Virginia,
this outburst happened at a community meeting

18:53.032 --> 18:54.734 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for a planned Islamic center.

18:54.767 --> 19:01.540 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: Nobody, nobody, nobody wants your evil
cult in this county. And I'll tell you. Let

19:01.574 --> 19:02.842 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
me tell you what.

19:02.875 --> 19:04.443 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

19:04.477 --> 19:07.947 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: I will do everything in my power to make
sure that doesn't -- does not happen.

19:07.980 --> 19:09.582 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: We don't want it.

19:09.615 --> 19:12.885 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: Because you are terrorists. Every one
of you are terrorists. I don't care what you

19:12.918 --> 19:14.587 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
say.

19:14.620 --> 19:17.857 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: A recent New York Times/CBS poll
found Americans more worried about a terrorist

19:17.890 --> 19:23.329 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
attack than at any time since 9/11, worries
that are also present in Muslim communities

19:23.362 --> 19:25.031 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
around the country.

19:25.064 --> 19:29.802 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Aya's family mosque, the Dar Al-Hijrah Center,
has been the target of violence. Last month,

19:29.835 --> 19:34.440 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
someone threw smoke bombs and a Molotov cocktail
over the fence in the middle of the night.

19:34.473 --> 19:38.944 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The mosque's leader, Imam Johari Abdul-Malik,
says they have been through this before and

19:38.978 --> 19:40.780 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
could almost see the violence coming.

19:40.813 --> 19:48.487 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
IMAM JOHARI ABDUL-MALIK, Dar Al-Hijrah Center:
We have this sense of a rising anti-Muslim-specific

19:48.521 --> 19:56.829 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
intolerance after the Paris attacks. This
community immediately went on high alert in

19:56.862 --> 19:58.998 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
preparation for a backlash.

19:59.031 --> 20:04.003 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Imam Johari invited us to stay
after evening prayers to speak with congregants.

20:04.036 --> 20:06.672 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Theraiah Hussein (ph) is a mother of six.

20:06.705 --> 20:12.144 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Everything changed, even starting from
my kids' school, because that's what we care

20:12.178 --> 20:16.549 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about, being called terrorists, being called
ISIS, and being called bad names. And that's

20:16.582 --> 20:18.184 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what really killed me.

20:18.217 --> 20:21.787 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALIK OSMAN, Student: Somebody just called
me a terrorist because they saw me walking.

20:21.821 --> 20:23.989 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: An adult person or another kid?

20:24.023 --> 20:30.729 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALIK OSMAN: A child. I was really scared
from then on. And that's why I don't wear

20:30.763 --> 20:32.398 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a head scarf.

20:32.431 --> 20:37.470 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: So, you don't wear a head scarf
because someone called you a terrorist? How

20:37.503 --> 20:39.438 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
does that make you feel?

20:39.472 --> 20:53.285 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALIK OSMAN: It makes me feel really angry,
like, awkward.

20:53.319 --> 21:02.795 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Aya's father, Badr, watched with
dread as the news of the San Bernardino attacks

21:02.828 --> 21:04.430 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
unfolded.

21:04.463 --> 21:07.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BADR LAOFIR, Father of Aya: We start praying
-- inside, I'm sure you would be doing the

21:07.700 --> 21:13.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
same thing -- that the shooter is not a Muslim,
but, of course, he's a Muslim. So, another

21:13.072 --> 21:19.378 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wave is going to start, and people, the media,
and every time, like every time.

21:19.411 --> 21:24.183 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Badr is vigilant about his family.
He has a strategy for the simplest of tasks,

21:24.216 --> 21:25.818 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
like the neighborhood walk.

21:25.851 --> 21:31.657 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BADR LAOFIR: I tell my wife and my daughter,
if she walks, she doesn't -- she needs to

21:31.690 --> 21:39.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
walk when a lot of people are around. And
a parking lot here, she's always with one

21:39.598 --> 21:46.038 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the -- my kids, always cell phone on hand.
Sometimes, people can attack you and follow

21:46.071 --> 21:49.208 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you and attack you even if -- in the place
where you live in.

21:49.241 --> 21:51.710 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
EDWIN ROESSLER, Fairfax County, Virginia,
Police Chief: Where there is fear and anxiety,

21:51.744 --> 21:56.415 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the role of law enforcement is to come in,
and to alleviate that and provide a sense

21:56.448 --> 21:58.217 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of security.

21:58.250 --> 22:01.954 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Fairfax County Police Chief Edwin
Roessler says after an attack like San Bernardino,

22:01.987 --> 22:03.689 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
local law enforcement must be proactive.

22:03.722 --> 22:09.061 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
EDWIN ROESSLER: And we contact the mosque
and we say, we're going to increase patrols.

22:09.094 --> 22:13.499 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Do you want us to show up at events? And it's
a two-way partnership.

22:13.532 --> 22:17.436 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Public officials across the U.S.
have asked the Muslim community to take a

22:17.469 --> 22:22.575 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lead role in addressing the issue of radicalization,
including President Obama in a prime-time

22:22.608 --> 22:24.310 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
address.

22:24.343 --> 22:25.978 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the United States:
Muslim leaders here and around the globe have

22:26.011 --> 22:31.550 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to continue working with us to decisively
and unequivocally reject the hateful ideology

22:31.584 --> 22:33.719 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that groups like ISIL and al-Qaida promote.

22:33.752 --> 22:35.187 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Not everyone agrees.

22:35.221 --> 22:37.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ROSA RAD, Washington, D.C., Resident: I find
it to be incredibly offensive.

22:37.223 --> 22:40.726 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
P.J. TOBIA: Rosa Rad, 23, lives in a trendy
Washington, D.C., neighborhood.

22:40.759 --> 22:45.464 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ROSA RAD: To have to be, like, vigilant and
have to be super aware of what's going on

22:45.497 --> 22:50.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is bizarre. I don't see any other communities
being given that responsibility. And I think

22:50.569 --> 22:54.373 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
